### =============================================================
### PRÁCTICA FINAL — BildyApp API
### REST Client (VS Code) — ejecuta en orden o por secciones
### =============================================================

### --- VARIABLES GLOBALES ---
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

# ⚠️  CAMBIA ESTE EMAIL ANTES DE CADA SESIÓN DE PRUEBAS NUEVA
# Si el usuario ya existe en la BD con rol guest, el paso 1.9 dará 403.
# Usa algo único, p.ej.: test1@bildy.com, test2@bildy.com, etc.
@email    = test01@ejemplo.com
@password = Bildy2026!

# Capturadas automáticamente tras login
@token         = {{login.response.body.token}}
@refreshToken  = {{login.response.body.refreshToken}}

# Rellena manualmente tras crear los recursos (copia el _id de la respuesta)
@clientId      = 69fb82878f2b4ea64657d229
@projectId     = 69fb82d78f2b4ea64657d236
@noteId        = 69fba3d497404e31d7bce7b6

# Código de verificación que llega al email (Mailtrap) o en consola de servidor
@verificationCode = 286363


### =============================================================
### SECCIÓN 0 — HEALTH CHECK (T11)
### =============================================================

### 0.1 Health check — servidor + MongoDB + uptime
GET http://localhost:3000/health


### =============================================================
### 🔍 CONSULTA RÁPIDA — ejecuta esto en cualquier momento
### para recuperar el token y ver los IDs de tus recursos
### =============================================================

### Q.1 Re-login — renueva @token sin re-registrarte
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### Q.2 Ver perfil + compañía del usuario actual
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Q.3 Ver todos los clientes (copia _id del que necesites → @clientId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/client?limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Q.4 Ver todos los proyectos (copia _id → @projectId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/project?limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Q.5 Ver todos los albaranes (copia _id → @noteId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/deliverynote?limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Q.6 Ver albaranes archivados / firmados
GET {{baseUrl}}/deliverynote?signed=true&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### =============================================================
### SECCIÓN 1 — USUARIOS (Práctica Intermedia, base obligatoria)
### =============================================================

### 1.1 Registro (201 Created)
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 1.2 Registro inválido — password corta (400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "no-es-email",
  "password": "123"
}

###

### 1.3 Registro duplicado (409 Conflict)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 1.4 Validar email con código correcto (200 OK)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/validation
Authorization: Bearer {{register.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "{{verificationCode}}"
}

###

### 1.5 Validar email con código incorrecto (400)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/validation
Authorization: Bearer {{register.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "000000"
}

###

### 1.6 Login correcto (200 OK — captura token automáticamente)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 1.7 Login incorrecto — contraseña errónea (401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword!"
}

###

### 1.8 Onboarding personal
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/register
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test01",
  "lastName": "BildyApp",
  "nif": "12347678Z"
}

###

### 1.9 Onboarding empresa — crear nueva compañía (admin/owner)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/company
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isFreelance": false,
  "name": "Boo Solutions S.L.",
  "cif": "B12061888",
  "address": {
    "street": "Calle de la Lada",
    "number": "42",
    "postal": "28001",
    "city": "Madrid",
    "province": "Madrid"
  }
}

###

### 1.10 Onboarding empresa — autónomo (isFreelance: true)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/company
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isFreelance": true
}

###

### 1.11 Subir logo de compañía (multipart)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/logo
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="logo"; filename="logo.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./mologo.png
--boundary--

###

### 1.12 Obtener perfil del usuario autenticado (con populate)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 1.13 Acceso sin token (401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/me

###

### 1.14 Refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.15 Logout (invalida refreshToken)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 1.16 Refresh tras logout — debe fallar (401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 1.17 Inyección NoSQL — debe ser sanitizada (400 / 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": { "$gt": "" },
  "password": "cualquiera"
}


